The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Wednesday, October 30, 2002 				 Le Roux, Leipus tips for Bengal 
 BY A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta: Bengals Ranji Trophy probables got a taste of the international-standard fitness regimen Tuesday, courtesy, Indian skipper Sourav Ganguly.																								Andrew Leipus and Adrian Le Roux, physio and physical trainer of the Indian team, respectively, spent nearly an hour with the Bengal players at the Eden in the afternoon.																								It was learnt that Sourav had asked the CAB officials whether they were interested in fitness-related inputs from the foreign professionals working with the Indian team. The CAB, in turn, didnt let this chance go.																								Le Roux will hand CAB authorities a written and detailed fitness-diet chart to be followed by the Bengal players. It is expected on Friday.																								Its great to have them among us. Any youngster aspiring to do well will find their instructions invaluable, said Deep Dasgupta, the former India wicketkeeper.
